Method Detail

precedes

public final boolean precedes(OrderList.Node<?> n)
Returns whether this node precedes the specified node in the OrderList that contains them. A node never precedes itself. The base node always precedes all others. The previous node of the base, if it is not the base itself (in an empty OrderList) is preceded by all others (i.e., is the last one).

Important: The result of this method is undefined if the nodes do not belong to the same OrderList instance.

Parameters:
n - another node
Returns:
whether this node precedes the specified node
